Introduction to ReactJS 
React is a JavaScript library used to build user interfaces (UI), especially for single-page 
applications. It allows developers to create reusable components and manage dynamic data 
efficiently. 
Key Features of React: 
 Component-based architecture 
 Virtual DOM for fast updates 
 One-way data binding 
 Reusable UI components 
