Render HTML in React 
Theory 
Rendering HTML means displaying content on a web page using React. 
In 
traditional 
HTML, we directly write HTML inside a file. 
In React, we use JavaScript to render HTML using: 
 ReactDOM.createRoot() 
 .render() method 
React renders content inside a root div (usually <div id="root"></div> in index.html). 
Important Points: 
 React uses a root element to display content. 
 The render() method displays elements on the web page. 
 React converts JSX/HTML into JavaScript objects internally. 
